(OSE)</li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Parochialism" title="Parochialism">Parochialism</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Posse_Comitatus_(organization)" title="Posse Comitatus (organization)">Posse Comitatus (organization)</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Regionalism_(politics)" title="Regionalism (politics)">Regionalism (politics)</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Secession" title="Secession">Secession</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Self-determination" title="Self-determination">Self-determination</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Self-sufficiency" title="Self-sufficiency">Self-sufficiency</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Think_globally,_act_locally" title="Think globally, act locally">Think globally, act locally</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Tribalism" title="Tribalism">Tribalism</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Localism_(politics)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: References">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist columns references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation journal">Ercan, S.A.; Hendriks, C.H. (2013). "The democratic challenges and potential of localism: Insights from deliberative democracy". <i>Policy Studies</i>. <b>31</b> (4): 422\xe2\x80\x93440. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1080%2F01442872.2013.822701">10.1080/01442872.2013.822701</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALocalism+%28politics%29&amp;rft.atitle=The+democratic+challenges+and+potential+of+localism%3A+Insights+from+deliberative+democracy&amp;rft.au=Hendriks%2C+C.H.&amp;rft.aufirst=S.A.&amp;rft.aulast=Ercan&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.jtitle=Policy+Studies&amp;rft.pages=422-440&amp;rft.volume=31&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1080%2F01442872.2013.822701&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFMilburn2004" class="citation"><a href="/wiki/Alan_Milburn" title="Alan Milburn">Milburn, Alan</a> (2004), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.demos.co.uk/catalogue/localism_page349.aspx"><i>Localism: The need for a new settlement</i></a> (speech), Demos</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALocalism+%28politics%29&amp;rft.aufirst=Alan&amp;rft.aulast=Milburn&amp;rft.btitle=Localism%3A+The+need+for+a+new+settlement&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pub=Demos&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.demos.co.uk%2Fcatalogue%2Flocalism_page349.aspx&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation news">Tomas, Mark. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.isj.org.uk/index.php4?id=176&amp;issue=109">"Feedback: Transport and climate change\xe2\x80\x94a reply to James Woodcock"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/International_Socialism_(magazine)" title="International Socialism (magazine)">International Socialism</a></i> (109).</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALocalism+%28politics%29&amp;rft.atitle=Feedback%3A+Transport+and+climate+change%E2%80%94a+reply+to+James+Woodcock&amp;rft.aufirst=Mark&amp;rft.aulast=Tomas&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.issue=109&amp;rft.jtitle=International+Socialism&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.isj.org.uk%2Findex.php4%3Fid%3D176%26issue%3D109&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.edwardgoldsmith.com/page78.html"><i>De-industrialising society</i></a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALocalism+%28politics%29&amp;rft.btitle=De-industrialising+society&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.edwardgoldsmith.com%2Fpage78.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.riverdeep.net/current/2000/10/103000_politic.jhtml"><i>Politic</i></a>, River Deep, October 2000</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALocalism+%28politics%29&amp;rft.btitle=Politic&amp;rft.date=2000-10&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pub=River+Deep&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.riverdeep.net%2Fcurrent%2F2000%2F10%2F103000_politic.jhtml&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFGeorge_Monbiot2003" class="citation"><a href="/wiki/George_Monbiot" title="George Monbiot">George Monbiot</a> (September 9, 2003), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.theguardian.com/comment/story/0,3604,1038164,00.html">"The myth of localism"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/The_Guardian" title="The Guardian">The Guardian</a></i></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALocalism+%28politics%29&amp;rft.atitle=The+myth+of+localism&amp;rft.au=George+Monbiot&amp;rft.btitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft.date=2003-09-09&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcomment%2Fstory%2F0%2C3604%2C1038164%2C00.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFMichaud2005" class="citation">Michaud, H\xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa8ne (April 2005), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www2.rnw.nl/rnw/en/specialseries/euexpansiondrive/050401euexp?view=Standard"><i>East-West brain drain</i></a>, Radio Netherlands</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALocalism+%28politics%29&amp;rft.aufirst=H%C3%A9l%C3%A8ne&amp;rft.aulast=Michaud&amp;rft.btitle=East-West+brain+drain&amp;rft.date=2005-04&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pub=Radio+Netherlands&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww2.rnw.nl%2Frnw%2Fen%2Fspecialseries%2Feuexpansiondrive%2F050401euexp%3Fview%3DStandard&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Edward J. Feser and Stuart H. Sweeney, <i>Out-migration, population decline, and regional economic distress</i>, Washington, DC: Economic Development Administration, 1998.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Hess-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Hess_9-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Hes